    long_description_en:
      "## Overview\nGugulipid is a natural extract derived from the resin of the Commiphora mukul tree. It is primarily used to support cardiovascular health by reducing cholesterol levels in the liver and functioning as a potent antioxidant. Additionally, Gugulipid is a valued component in dietary regimens due to its effects in aiding fat reduction and promoting overall heart wellness.\n\n## Key Benefits\n\n| Benefit           | Description                                                                 |\n|-------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| Health Impact     | Gugulipid significantly decreases cholesterol production, promoting heart health and preventing atherosclerosis. |\n| Natural Healing   | It works by activating specific receptors in the body naturally to balance cholesterol levels. |\n| Daily Wellness    | Regular use of Gugulipid can help maintain optimal lipid profiles and support weight management. |\n| Quality Assurance | Extracted following stringent guidelines to ensure purity and potency, and tested for consistency and safety. |\n\n## Traditional Usage\n* **Historical background in Ayurveda**: Gugulipid has been used in traditional Ayurvedic medicine for centuries as a remedy for a variety of ailments, particularly those affecting the heart and circulation.\n* **Traditional applications**: Traditionally employed to address arthritis, obesity, and lipid disorders.\n* **Cultural significance**: Revered in Indian culture for its holistic healing properties and as a sacred resin used in rituals and incense.\n\n## Key Ingredients\n1. **Commiphora Mukul Extract**\n   * Properties: Cholesterol-busting, anti-inflammatory, antioxidant\n   * Benefits: Helps lower LDL (bad cholesterol), supports joint health, and enhances metabolic rate.\n\n2. **Plant Sterols**\n   * Properties: Cholesterol absorption blocker, immune system support\n   * Benefits: Inhibit cholesterol uptake in the intestines, contributing to reduced total cholesterol and LDL levels.\n\n## Usage Instructions\n1. **Recommended Dosage**: 500 mg, twice daily with meals.\n2. **Best Time**: Morning and evening, ideally with meals to enhance absorption.\n3. **Method**: Swallow with a glass of water.\n4. **Duration**: Use consistently for a minimum of 12 weeks to observe significant changes in cholesterol levels.\n\n## Safety Information\n> **Important Notice**: Individuals with thyroid disorders should consult a healthcare provider before using Gugulipid, as it may affect thyroid hormone levels.\n\n### Precautions\n* Pregnant or breastfeeding women should avoid use unless advised by a healthcare professional.\n* Individuals with liver disorders or those taking cholesterol-lowering medications should consult their healthcare provider.\n* Not recommended for children under 18.\n\n## Scientific Background\nRecent studies have shown:\n* Gugulipid can significantly reduce serum LDL cholesterol by enhancing LDL receptor-binding activity.\n* Trials have shown an effective reduction in triglyceride levels, promoting cardiovascular health.\n* Research indicates its role in oxidative stress reduction, thus delaying the onset of fatty plaque formation in arteries.\n\n---",
